WEBVTT

00:58.224 --> 01:00.267
Emily!

03:02.265 --> 03:04.600
You're the medical examiner?

03:28.416 --> 03:30.459
Mr. Rose?

04:28.309 --> 04:29.643
l'm sorry, Mr. Rose. ..

04:31.813 --> 04:34.273
. ..but l cannot state conclusively...

04:34.440 --> 04:39.403
. ..that the cause of death
was natural.

04:40.530 --> 04:42.864
Your daughter, she. . . .

04:57.171 --> 04:59.214
Excuse me, Father?

05:00.008 --> 05:01.883
Father Moore.

05:03.261 --> 05:04.594
You'll have to come with me.

05:14.063 --> 05:16.565
-Father Moore!
-Will you plead guilty?

05:16.733 --> 05:19.318
-Tell us about the exorcism!
-Over here, Father Moore!

05:19.485 --> 05:22.738
We're at Crescent County Courthouse.
We show you Father Richard Moore. . . .

05:22.905 --> 05:25.574
-What about the parents?
-They're not talking to the police.

05:25.742 --> 05:26.908
Do we charge them?

05:27.076 --> 05:29.286
No. Even the priest admits
he ran the show.

05:29.454 --> 05:31.121
We need a Christian on this.

05:31.289 --> 05:32.539
Preferably a Catholic.

05:32.707 --> 05:34.791
Somebody that knows this shit
inside out. ..

05:34.959 --> 05:37.961
. ..and who the public will see
as unbiased.

05:38.921 --> 05:41.256
We're going after a holy man here.

05:42.425 --> 05:44.092
Ethan Thomas.

05:45.094 --> 05:48.764
He's not Catholic, though.
Methodist, l think.

05:48.931 --> 05:52.434
But the guy practically lives at church.
Choir, teaches Sunday school.

05:52.602 --> 05:55.771
He's no choirboy in the courtroom.
l've seen him tear people up.

05:56.064 --> 05:58.065
He's a shrewd son of a bitch.

06:01.903 --> 06:05.655
All right, pull him off whatever
he's doing. He's lead prosecutor.

06:26.552 --> 06:30.347
There's ambition. She never stops.
She even works while she drinks.

06:30.515 --> 06:32.557
-Gentlemen, you know Erin Bruner.
-Of course.

06:32.725 --> 06:35.018
-Hello.
-l was so sure Van Hopper would fry...

06:35.186 --> 06:37.979
. ..but you proved me wrong, lady.

06:38.147 --> 06:39.481
The system worked, that's all.

06:40.858 --> 06:43.402
Gentlemen, you'll excuse us,
will you?

06:43.861 --> 06:45.654
Have you seen the news
about this priest?

06:45.822 --> 06:49.491
l heard something about an exorcism
gone bad, but l don't know the details.

06:49.659 --> 06:52.119
The DA charged him
with negligent homicide.

06:52.286 --> 06:55.705
They offered a very reasonable plea
bargain, but the priest turned it down.

06:55.873 --> 06:57.124
Do not ask me to take this--

06:57.291 --> 07:00.544
The archdiocese
specifically requested you.

07:01.170 --> 07:04.339
-Why me?
-They followed the Van Hopper trial.

07:04.507 --> 07:06.174
They think you're smart...

07:06.342 --> 07:07.759
. ..and convincing.

07:08.302 --> 07:10.429
They want you to ask the priest
to reconsider.

07:10.596 --> 07:11.847
Well, what if he won't?

07:12.014 --> 07:14.975
This sounds like a quagmire.
lf l'm smart, l'll leave it alone.

07:16.060 --> 07:19.271
Erin, the Van Hopper case
got you back on the fast track.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.481
Once again, you're a rising star.

07:21.649 --> 07:25.235
-Chivas, neat, please.
-Tanqueray martini, dry.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.780
-What are you saying?
-l'm saying, you do this for me. . .

07:29.198 --> 07:31.992
. ..and the rising star keeps rising.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.410
The case is yours.

07:36.205 --> 07:39.124
And just how high
do l get to rise this time?

07:41.377 --> 07:43.712
l've been junior partner
for too long now, Karl.

07:43.880 --> 07:46.047
-lt's not like other firms haven't called.
-Erin--

07:46.215 --> 07:50.135
l want my name on the door,
right next to yours.

07:53.055 --> 07:54.723
Okay.

07:54.891 --> 07:56.099
Try to get the deal.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.518
lf the priest won't
and this goes to trial...

07:58.686 --> 08:01.188
. ..the archdiocese feels he could
be an embarrassment.

08:01.355 --> 08:03.273
So under no circumstances
is he to testify.

08:03.441 --> 08:05.859
No, of course.
lf l'd put Van Hopper on the stand. . .

08:06.027 --> 08:10.071
. ..he'd be marking time on death row
instead of sunbathing in Miami.

08:10.239 --> 08:11.615
His tab.

08:36.890 --> 08:39.226
Good morning, l'm Erin Bruner.

08:40.269 --> 08:41.852
May l sit down?

08:43.563 --> 08:46.942
They brought the chair
for my public defender.

08:48.402 --> 08:52.906
l guess they left it when they decided
l wasn't going to kill myself with it.

09:01.541 --> 09:04.459
My firm represents the archdiocese.

09:06.128 --> 09:07.462
Yes.

09:07.964 --> 09:11.132
Yes, l was expecting them
to send someone.

09:12.134 --> 09:14.928
-Why did they choose you?
-l wanted this case.

09:15.096 --> 09:18.557
-So you like the spotlight?
-l'm used to it.

09:18.724 --> 09:20.308
l defended James Van Hopper.

09:20.810 --> 09:22.936
And now you've come
to further your celebrity.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.354
No.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.691
l'm here to make senior partner
at my firm.

09:30.778 --> 09:33.488
-Are you a Catholic?
-No.

09:33.656 --> 09:36.992
l'm an agnostic, l guess.
l'm not really sure.

09:37.159 --> 09:38.994
lf you're not sure, then you are one.

09:41.038 --> 09:44.624
l don't think you're the right attorney.
l'll stick with my public defender.

09:44.792 --> 09:47.294
He can't get the DA
to get you a better deal. l can.

09:47.461 --> 09:49.337
l won't be making
any plea agreement.

09:49.505 --> 09:51.798
lf you don't, the archdiocese
won't post your bail.

09:51.966 --> 09:54.050
You'll be stuck in here for the trial.

09:56.971 --> 09:59.222
Do you understand how long
they can put you away?

09:59.390 --> 10:00.640
lt's been explained to me.

10:00.808 --> 10:04.269
The DA's office doesn't like it when
religion holds itself above the law.

10:04.437 --> 10:06.021
And this prosecutor,
Ethan Thomas?

10:06.188 --> 10:09.024
You're gonna need somebody
hungry and smart.. .

10:09.191 --> 10:11.026
. ..and aggressive
to even have a chance.

10:11.193 --> 10:14.738
What would your strategy be to defend
me against such a formidable man?

10:15.156 --> 10:17.365
-That depends.
-On what?

10:17.533 --> 10:18.908
On how you wanna be defended.

10:23.664 --> 10:27.083
What's your main concern,
other than staying out of jail?

10:27.251 --> 10:30.754
-ls it how you're being portrayed?
-l don't care about my reputation.

10:30.921 --> 10:32.797
l'm not afraid of jail.

10:35.301 --> 10:38.678
What l care about
is telling Emily Rose's story.

10:39.805 --> 10:42.307
l want people to hear
what only l can tell.

10:42.475 --> 10:44.184
And what is that?

10:44.352 --> 10:45.935
What really happened to Emily. ..

10:46.103 --> 10:48.063
. ..and why.

10:51.442 --> 10:53.693
lf l let you defend me. . .

10:53.861 --> 10:57.906
. ..will you promise to let me testify and
tell the truth about what happened?

10:58.658 --> 11:03.244
And what is the truth you would tell?
That the ritual killed her?

11:03.788 --> 11:05.914
-Was it your fault she died?
-No.

11:06.082 --> 11:08.166
All right.
Then l'll let you tell her story.

11:08.334 --> 11:12.087
But only if you agree to let me do
whatever else it takes to win.

11:30.898 --> 11:33.942
You're not used to
this kind of place.

11:34.694 --> 11:38.405
l'm sure our life is very strange
to you.

11:40.116 --> 11:42.117
Not so strange.

11:43.327 --> 11:45.787
l grew up in a little town.

11:45.955 --> 11:48.748
But our house wasn't as nice
or as big as this.

11:48.916 --> 11:50.917
My mother, she raised me alone.

11:51.085 --> 11:53.962
She was a schoolteacher,
so we had very little money.

11:54.130 --> 11:56.423
What a wonderful thing to be.

11:57.174 --> 12:00.218
That was Emily's dream,
to be a teacher.

12:00.636 --> 12:04.097
That's why she went away
to the university.

12:11.439 --> 12:13.523
A lot of cats live here.

12:14.984 --> 12:17.152
There are. . .

12:17.319 --> 12:19.988
. .. 1 1 now, l think.

12:20.156 --> 12:21.698
Emily always brought them home.

12:21.866 --> 12:26.703
Ever since she was a little girl,
she couldn't leave a stray abandoned.

12:30.416 --> 12:32.792
Before these troubles began...

12:32.960 --> 12:34.335
. ..was Emily a happy girl?

12:34.962 --> 12:36.504
Oh, yes.

12:37.381 --> 12:39.924
Before she went away
to university...

12:40.092 --> 12:42.927
. ..my Emily was so very happy.

12:44.930 --> 12:47.932
What is going on--? Girls!

12:51.020 --> 12:52.896
Mama.

12:54.899 --> 12:56.357
ls it--?

12:57.735 --> 12:59.194
lt's a scholarship, Mama.

13:00.571 --> 13:03.364
They pay for it.
They pay for everything.

13:04.366 --> 13:05.825
This is your dream, Emily.

13:07.828 --> 13:09.579
You'll be leaving us.

13:10.956 --> 13:12.707
lt's okay.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.711
l'll be okay.

13:17.379 --> 13:19.839
l'm gonna show this to your father.

13:27.932 --> 13:31.351
-Counselor. Thanks for meeting me.
-Sure.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.730
Can l buy you a drink, Mr. Thomas?
He makes an excellent martini.

13:35.898 --> 13:37.857
Just water for me, please.

13:38.400 --> 13:39.859
So...

13:40.027 --> 13:42.862
. ..the judge thinks we should offer
a new plea agreement.

13:43.781 --> 13:47.200
She feels the community might be
better served without this trial.

13:47.368 --> 13:49.536
How do you feel about it?

13:49.703 --> 13:51.412
Personally.

13:51.997 --> 13:54.457
My job is to represent
the interests of the people.. .

13:54.625 --> 13:56.334
. ..and make an effort to be objective.

13:58.754 --> 14:00.588
l ask because l know
you're a churchgoer.

14:00.756 --> 14:02.590
Now you're set to prosecute
a man of God.

14:03.092 --> 14:05.093
Your priest broke the law. . .

14:05.261 --> 14:07.303
. ..and a young girl is dead.

14:08.222 --> 14:11.432
lf he's a man of God, then, personally,
l think he's even more subject.. .

14:11.600 --> 14:15.270
. ..to the laws of moral behavior.
lf it were up to me, he'd get no deal.

14:15.437 --> 14:19.190
And forgiveness and compassion?
lsn't that part of your creed?

14:19.358 --> 14:21.359
Or does that just get in the way
of your work?

14:24.738 --> 14:26.948
lf you have compassion
for your client. . .

14:27.116 --> 14:29.450
. ..you'll persuade him to accept this:

14:29.618 --> 14:31.953
Charges reduced
to reckless endangerment.

14:32.121 --> 14:34.247
Twelve months in a county jail.

14:34.415 --> 14:36.833
Reducible to six, plus probation,
if he stays out of trouble.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.710
Somehow l expect
he can manage that.

14:39.587 --> 14:42.922
But please understand me.
lf he refuses, l will seek the maximum.

14:43.340 --> 14:46.134
Father Moore has made it clear
there will be no plea agreement.

14:46.302 --> 14:49.137
He will not lie or admit to something
he is not guilty of.

14:49.305 --> 14:52.807
-And he was never neglectful of Emily.
-"Never neglectful"?

14:52.975 --> 14:54.809
Have you seen
the postmortem photographs?

14:59.231 --> 15:02.984
We'll go to trial. My client wants
the public to know the truth.

15:03.777 --> 15:05.445
Good.

15:06.488 --> 15:08.364
So do l.

15:09.992 --> 15:12.118
Have a good night, counselor.

16:21.480 --> 16:25.149
Let the record show that the defendant
and his counsel are present. . .

16:25.317 --> 16:27.026
. ..and that the jury is seated.

16:27.569 --> 16:31.364
-Mr. Thomas, you may begin.
-Thank you, Your Honor.

16:31.532 --> 16:34.617
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.
My name is Ethan Thomas.

16:34.785 --> 16:38.246
l'm the assistant district attorney,
and l represent the people.

16:38.414 --> 16:40.832
ln the case before you,
the evidence will show...

16:41.000 --> 16:45.712
. ..that the victim had a serious medical
condition that demanded treatment.

16:45.879 --> 16:50.091
We will prove that the victim's
condition rendered her physically. . .

16:50.259 --> 16:55.263
. ..and psychologically incapable
of caring for herself.

16:55.431 --> 16:56.973
Her care...

16:57.141 --> 16:58.891
. ..was then wholly entrusted.. .

16:59.393 --> 17:03.271
. ..to that man, the defendant,
Father Richard Moore.

17:03.439 --> 17:06.065
She became his responsibility...

17:07.026 --> 17:09.902
. ..and he betrayed
that responsibility...

17:10.069 --> 17:12.613
. ..by persuading her to abandon
her medical treatment...

17:12.781 --> 17:15.282
. ..in favor of religious treatment:

17:15.992 --> 17:19.619
A ritual exorcism,
performed by the defendant. . .

17:19.788 --> 17:24.791
. ..allegedly to cure the victim
by ridding her of demonic forces.

17:25.419 --> 17:29.088
We will demonstrate
that this course of action. . .

17:29.256 --> 17:32.216
. ..directly resulted
in the victim's death.

17:33.135 --> 17:35.344
l said a moment ago
that l represent the people.

17:35.512 --> 17:38.598
We all know what that means,
but it's a little abstract, isn't it?

17:39.099 --> 17:41.309
Miss Bruner,
the attorney for the defense. . .

17:41.477 --> 17:44.312
. ..is seated right next
to the man she represents.

17:44.480 --> 17:47.815
And l stand here
to represent the people.

17:49.318 --> 17:51.277
That's not really why
l stand here today.

17:52.488 --> 17:55.990
l'm here on behalf of someone
who can't sit at a table. . .

17:57.159 --> 18:00.411
. ..and look at you every day
and gain your sympathy...

18:01.038 --> 18:03.831
. ..someone who can't take the stand
to testify...

18:03.999 --> 18:07.335
. ..and tell you what happened
in her own words.

18:09.671 --> 18:11.172
A young girl. . .

18:11.340 --> 18:13.299
. ..that could've been your daughter.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.802
Could've been mine.

18:15.969 --> 18:19.889
A girl who trusted
Father Richard Moore with her life.

18:26.730 --> 18:28.106
This is what she looked like. . .

18:31.360 --> 18:35.696
. ..before the defendant began
his religious treatment.

18:38.200 --> 18:41.244
This is a photograph taken of her
on the day that she died.

18:56.051 --> 19:00.888
l stand here for Emily Rose.. .

19:02.182 --> 19:04.892
. ..who died horribly...

19:05.060 --> 19:07.979
. ..at age 1 9.

19:09.731 --> 19:13.401
You won't be able to see Emily sitting
here day after day during this trial.

19:13.861 --> 19:16.654
But l hope you'll remember her
as she was when she was alive. . .

19:18.490 --> 19:20.032
. ..and full of. . .

19:21.410 --> 19:24.245
. ..hopes and dreams.

19:26.165 --> 19:30.084
And as she was when Father
Richard Moore was finished with her...

19:31.336 --> 19:32.879
. ..and left her to die.

19:36.133 --> 19:37.884
Thank you.

19:38.802 --> 19:42.096
ls the defense prepared
to make its opening statement?

19:45.017 --> 19:47.101
l'd like to reserve
my opening statement...

19:47.269 --> 19:49.562
. ..until the presentation
of the defense's case.

19:49.730 --> 19:51.522
As is your privilege.

19:52.107 --> 19:54.400
Prosecution may begin.

19:54.568 --> 19:56.068
That was already my plan.

19:56.236 --> 19:58.779
Thank you, Your Honor.
The people call Dr. Edith Vogel.

19:58.947 --> 20:03.701
l've known Emily her entire life.
l took care of all of the Rose girls.

20:03.869 --> 20:06.954
Can you describe Emily
as you knew her growing up?

20:07.122 --> 20:09.457
She was a bit sickly
in her early years.

20:09.625 --> 20:14.295
She stayed inside a lot,
reading, learning music.

20:14.796 --> 20:16.464
How did she feel about
going to school?

20:16.632 --> 20:18.633
Objection.
The witness is not a psychiatrist.

20:18.800 --> 20:21.969
l'll rephrase. Did you talk to Emily
about going off to college?

20:22.137 --> 20:24.680
Yes. She told me she was excited. . .

20:24.848 --> 20:29.352
. ..but nervous that she would be away
from her family in the big city.

20:29.519 --> 20:31.562
This was an overwhelming change
for her.

20:31.730 --> 20:33.606
Did you stay in touch
after she went away?

20:33.774 --> 20:39.195
Yes. She wrote me a letter
saying that she'd been to a dance...

20:39.363 --> 20:41.447
. ..and she'd met a boy
named Jason.

20:41.823 --> 20:43.699
She didn't want her mother
to know this. . .

20:43.867 --> 20:46.410
. ..because her mother did not
approve of dancing. . .

20:46.578 --> 20:48.663
. ..and had warned her
about the boys at school.

20:48.830 --> 20:52.625
Did Emily communicate with you again
last fall after you received the letter?

20:52.793 --> 20:54.418
Actually, it was her mother.

20:56.922 --> 20:58.506
She telephoned me. . .

20:58.674 --> 21:01.342
. ..waking me out of a deep sleep
at 4 in the morning.

21:02.761 --> 21:07.139
She asked me to call Emily at
a payphone on the university campus.

21:10.018 --> 21:13.229
When Emily answered,
she was quite hysterical.

21:15.023 --> 21:17.858
At first, she just
sobbed uncontrollably.

21:18.527 --> 21:22.071
But eventually she calmed down
enough to tell me what happened.

21:23.991 --> 21:26.534
She said that she was alone
that weekend.

21:26.702 --> 21:29.287
Her roommate had gone home.

21:33.333 --> 21:35.376
She had awakened...

21:36.295 --> 21:39.297
...and thought she smelled
something burning.

21:40.299 --> 21:42.925
There was no alarm,
but she got up...

21:43.719 --> 21:45.886
...afraid there was a fire.

24:50.322 --> 24:53.073
Dr. Mueller, what's your position
at the university hospital?

24:53.241 --> 24:55.910
l am chairman of
the Department of Neurology.

24:56.077 --> 24:58.370
And after you heard
about the dorm-room incident. ..

24:58.538 --> 25:00.122
. ..what were your initial thoughts?

25:00.290 --> 25:03.417
At first, l thought perhaps
Emily had taken illegal drugs.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.419
Some type of hallucinogen.

25:05.587 --> 25:09.465
But we ran tests and found no trace
of drugs in her system.

25:09.633 --> 25:11.926
And the more she explained
the incident to me...

25:12.093 --> 25:15.304
. ..the more l began to suspect
something else.

25:15.472 --> 25:19.975
Epilepsy results from uncontrolled
electrical activity in the brain.

25:20.894 --> 25:22.895
ln a severe, or grand mal, seizure...

25:23.063 --> 25:25.606
...a person may lose consciousness
for several minutes...

25:25.774 --> 25:29.109
...and suffer involuntary contractions
of all the muscles of the body.

25:29.277 --> 25:31.737
ls it possible for a person
suffering such a seizure...

25:31.905 --> 25:35.241
...to have hallucinations or perceive
the things that Emily described?

25:35.408 --> 25:38.953
The muscle contractions could feel
like an extreme pressure on the body.

25:39.120 --> 25:41.956
And it is certainly possible,
with all that brain activity...

25:42.123 --> 25:46.418
. ..for a person to perceive all sorts
of strange and violent things.

25:46.836 --> 25:50.130
So suspecting that Emily was
epileptic, how did you proceed?

25:50.298 --> 25:52.550
l administered
an electroencephalograph.

25:52.717 --> 25:53.968
What did the EEG reveal?

25:54.135 --> 25:58.597
lt showed a possible epileptic focus
in the patient's left temporal lobe.

25:58.765 --> 26:00.558
Did this require a specific treatment?

26:00.725 --> 26:03.894
Yes, l began a medication schedule
for Emily with the drug Gambutrol.

26:04.062 --> 26:08.148
l also advised regular follow-up
examinations and further tests.

26:08.316 --> 26:11.318
But Emily failed to keep
her follow-up appointments with me.

26:11.945 --> 26:14.572
She give any reason for discontinuing
these appointments?

26:14.739 --> 26:18.450
Yes, she told me she was convinced
that her condition was a spiritual one.

26:18.618 --> 26:22.913
lt was the conviction of her priest,
she said, and she shared his beliefs.

26:23.081 --> 26:25.666
Was it your impression
that Emily had placed her care. ..

26:25.834 --> 26:27.751
-. . .entirely--?
-Leading the witness.

26:28.128 --> 26:29.378
Sustained.

26:32.007 --> 26:33.549
After the end of October...

26:33.717 --> 26:36.051
. ..did you ask Emily
why she had stopped. . .

26:36.219 --> 26:37.928
. ..filling her Gambutrol
prescriptions?

26:38.096 --> 26:42.516
Yes. She said that Father Moore had
suggested she stop taking the drug.

26:42.684 --> 26:44.351
And what, in your medical opinion. . .

26:44.519 --> 26:46.770
. ..was the result
of Father Moore's suggestion?

26:46.938 --> 26:49.106
l believe Father Moore's suggestion
killed her.

26:49.274 --> 26:50.691
Objection, Your Honor!

26:50.859 --> 26:54.194
The witness is asserting outrageous
conclusions based on pure hearsay.

26:54.863 --> 26:59.533
Technically correct, but l'll allow it
as part of his expert opinion testimony.

26:59.701 --> 27:01.452
Thank you, Dr. Mueller.

27:01.620 --> 27:02.870
Your witness.

27:03.038 --> 27:08.042
You said you observed a possible
epileptic focus in the temporal lobe.

27:08.209 --> 27:11.879
Doesn't this imply what you observed
may not have been an epileptic focus?

27:12.047 --> 27:13.672
Yes, that's also possible.

27:13.840 --> 27:17.009
Would Father Moore's advice to stop
