if she'd continued her treatment.

43:06.000 --> 43:08.793
ln your opinion, if Emily
had continued with her medication...

43:08.961 --> 43:11.462
-. . .would she be alive today?
-Absolutely.

43:11.630 --> 43:17.010
lf treated early, psychotic epileptic
disorder is rarely fatal.

43:17.177 --> 43:18.845
l mean, this--

43:19.013 --> 43:22.348
This was a very sick girl.

43:22.683 --> 43:25.226
The defendant should've realized
that Emily was in need. ..

43:25.394 --> 43:28.146
. ..of continued medical treatment.

43:29.023 --> 43:31.983
Thank you, doctor. Your witness.

43:34.903 --> 43:38.948
Doctor, you testified that Gambutrol
could've controlled Emily's condition.

43:39.658 --> 43:40.867
How do you know that?

43:41.035 --> 43:44.662
lt's the inevitable result
of taking the drug.

43:44.830 --> 43:46.706
lt would've controlled
her seizures. . .

43:46.874 --> 43:48.916
. ..which were the root cause
of her psychosis.

43:49.084 --> 43:52.045
But wasn't Emily still experiencing
psychotic symptoms. ..

43:52.212 --> 43:54.380
. ..even after she started
taking the medication?

43:54.548 --> 43:57.425
Yes. Because Gambutrol
has a cumulative effect.

43:57.593 --> 43:59.719
lt takes time to build up
in the system.

43:59.887 --> 44:03.264
You assume that Gambutrol would've
helped her, but you don't know.

44:03.432 --> 44:05.725
lt's a reasonable assumption, but. ...

44:06.226 --> 44:07.810
No, of course, l can't be certain.

44:09.396 --> 44:14.776
Doctor, is "psychotic epileptic
disorder" a common medical term...

44:14.943 --> 44:16.569
. ..or did you just make it up?

44:17.321 --> 44:19.822
